ACTIVE
======

VIM
gh:       select mode
<C-g>:    (from Visual Mode) select mode

TERMINAL
ctrl+a or Home:   Moves the cursor to the start of a line.
ctrl+e or End:    Moves the cursor to the end of a line.
esc+b:    Moves to the beginning of the previous or current word.
esc+f:    Moves forward one word at a time. (same as alt+f)
ctrl+k:   Deletes from the current cursor position to the end of the line.
ctrl+u:   Deletes from the start of the line to the current cursor position.
ctrl+w:   Deletes the word before the cursor.
alt+b:    Goes back one word at a time.
alt+f:    Moves forward one word at a time. (this doesn't work due to the menu bar)
alt+c:    Capitalizes letter where cursor is and moves to end of word.
ctrl+/:   Undo
esc+.:    insert last command
ctrl+y:   paste text cut from ctrl+u/k
alt+d:    deletes word (same as esc+d)

ARCHIVED
========
# for commands that have been mastered or dumped
ctrl-G:   displays name of file
ctrl-A:   goes to next number on same line and increments it
ctrl-x:     decrements number
crtl-z:   suspends
          fg from shell to return to foreground

NOTE: consider adding "set -o vi" to .bashrc
